    "body": "this may not be doing what you expect, with current master\n(this was just fixed very recently via https://github.com/pydata/pandas/pull/5723)\n\nYou setting with a scalar when their is no index, does not work (hmm...maybe I should raise on this)\n\n```\nIn [1]: df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['a', 'b', 'c c'])\n\nIn [2]: df\nOut[2]: \nEmpty DataFrame\nColumns: [a, b, c c]\nIndex: []\n\n[0 rows x 3 columns]\n```\n\nThis will now raise\n\n```\nIn [3]: df['d'] = 3\n```\n\nSelection works fine\n\n```\nIn [4]: df\nOut[4]: \nEmpty DataFrame\nColumns: [a, b, c c]\nIndex: []\n\n[0 rows x 4 columns]\n\nIn [5]: df['c c']\nOut[5]: Series([], name: c c, dtype: object)\n\nIn [6]: pd.__version__\nOut[6]: '0.13.0rc1-99-gbac7c6e'\n\n```\n"
